ciscoAtmTrunkStatMIB.description: The MIB module contains ATM Trunk statistics. TERMINOLOGY ----------- PVC: Permanent Virtual Circuit OAM: Operation and Management CRC: Cyclic redundancy check AIS: Alarm Indication Signal TDM: Time Division Multiplex FERF: Far End Receive Failure CPS: Common Part Sub-layer PDU: Protocol Data Unit HEC: Header Error Control DSP: Digital Signal Processing CID: Channel Identifier UUI: User-to-User Information VoIP: Voice over IP CCS: Common Channel Signaling VoAAL2: Voice over AAL2 SDU: Service Data Unit HDLC: High Level Data Link Control SAR: Segmantation and Reassembly External AIS - is an Alarm Indication Signal associated with a maintenance alarm detected on a defective maintenance span, that is transmitted in the direction of the defect as a substitute for normal signal. The purpose is to show the downstream entities that a defect has been identified and to prevent other maintenance alarms consequent to this first defect. External AIS bit stream is represented by an all 1's signal. Ref - ITU-T Rec. M.20 sec. 5.4.2 a External RAI - is a Remote Alarm Indication signal that is transmitted upstream from an entity that has detected defects persisting long enough to constitute a received signal failure. Its purpose is to report in the backward direction that there is an interruption of service in the forward direction. The forward direction is from the originating end of the alarm to the remote end. The backward direction is from the remote end to the orginating end of the alarm. Ref - ITU-T Rec. G.704 section 2.1.3.1.3 I.366.2 - ANNEX N External Connection AIS - is a Alarm Indicating Signal transmitted in the downstream direction from the AAL type 2 connecting point that first detects a defect affecting the AAL type 2 connection; this includes defects indicated by lower layers. Ref - ITU-T Rec. I.610 sec 6.2.2.1.1.1 External Connection RDI - is a signal transmitted upstream by an AAl type 2 endpoint that is in an alarm state as the result of having received an AAL type2 connection AIS or having detected a defect that affects the AAL type2 connection. All ATM alarm definitions are specified in I.610 (ITU standard).

catsPvcHistoryTable.name: catsPvcHistoryTable
catsPvcHistoryTable.description: This table represents a 24 hour history of statistics per PVC. The statistics are collected using 15 minute intervals. Entries in this table are populated at the end of the interval.

catsPvcHistoryEntry.name: catsPvcHistoryEntry
catsPvcHistoryEntry.description: An entry in the table. Each entry represents the PVC statistics for a given 15 minute interval. The ifIndex refers to the instance in the ifTable with ifType propAtm(197) or atm(37).

catsPvcVpi.name: catsPvcVpi
catsPvcVpi.description: The VPI value for the PVC for which the statistics are being collected.

catsPvcVci.name: catsPvcVci
catsPvcVci.description: The VCI value for the PVC for which the statistics are being collected.

catsPvcIntervalIndex.name: catsPvcIntervalIndex
catsPvcIntervalIndex.description: This is the history interval number. The intervals are 15 minutes long and thus for a 24 hour period there will be 96 intervals. The 24 hour interval is aligned to wall clock. The index of 1 will represent the interval from 00:00 to 00:15. The index of 2 will represent the interval from 00:15 to 00:30 and so on.

catsPvcValidFlag.name: catsPvcValidFlag
catsPvcValidFlag.description: This object is used to indicate if the entry has valid statistics data. It contains a value of true(1) if the data is valid and false(2) otherwise. A possible scenario when this flag will be set to false(2) is when there are time changes due to daylight savings time and/ or time zone changes. This flag can also be set to false(2) if the statistics in this 15 minute interval have experienced discontinuity.

catsPvcDiscontinuityTime.name: catsPvcDiscontinuityTime
catsPvcDiscontinuityTime.description: This object will represent the timestamp when the statistics in this 15 minute interval were discontinued due to a forced clear on the module. If this has the default value then it indicates that the statistics in this interval have not experienced any discontinuity.

catsPvcAtmXmtCells.name: catsPvcAtmXmtCells
catsPvcAtmXmtCells.description: The total number of cells transmitted by this PVC towards the ATM network.

catsPvcAtmRcvCells.name: catsPvcAtmRcvCells
catsPvcAtmRcvCells.description: The total number of cells received by this PVC from the ATM network.

catsPvcAvgAtmXmtCells.name: catsPvcAvgAtmXmtCells
catsPvcAvgAtmXmtCells.description: The average number of cells transmitted towards the network by this PVC. The average is computed by dividing the total number of cells transmitted over this 15 minute interval by the interval time (15 minutes).

catsPvcAvgAtmRcvCells.name: catsPvcAvgAtmRcvCells
catsPvcAvgAtmRcvCells.description: The average number of cells received from the network by the PVC. The average is computed by dividing the total number of cells received over this 15 minute interval by the interval time (15 minutes).

catsPvcPeakAtmXmtCells.name: catsPvcPeakAtmXmtCells
catsPvcPeakAtmXmtCells.description: The peak number of cells per second transmitted towards the network. The transmitted cells per second are monitored every second and the peak value over this 15 minute interval is returned in this object.

catsPvcPeakAtmRcvCells.name: catsPvcPeakAtmRcvCells
catsPvcPeakAtmRcvCells.description: The peak number of cells per second received from the network. The received cells per second are monitored every second and the peak value over this 15 minute interval is returned in this object.

catsPvcOamXmtEndLpbkCells.name: catsPvcOamXmtEndLpbkCells
catsPvcOamXmtEndLpbkCells.description: The number of OAM end-to-end loopback cells that were transmitted on this connection during this 15 minute interval.

catsPvcOamRcvEndLpbkCells.name: catsPvcOamRcvEndLpbkCells
catsPvcOamRcvEndLpbkCells.description: The number of OAM end-to-end loopback cells that were received on this connection during this 15 minute interval.

catsPvcOamXmtSegLpbkCells.name: catsPvcOamXmtSegLpbkCells
catsPvcOamXmtSegLpbkCells.description: The number of OAM Segment loop back cells that were transmitted on this connection during this 15 minute interval.

catsPvcOamRcvSegLpbkCells.name: catsPvcOamRcvSegLpbkCells
catsPvcOamRcvSegLpbkCells.description: The number of OAM Segment loop back cells that were received on this connection during this 15 minute interval.

catsPvcOamLpbkLostCells.name: catsPvcOamLpbkLostCells
catsPvcOamLpbkLostCells.description: This object keeps track of the number of OAM loopback cells lost.

catsPvcDiscardedRcvOamCells.name: catsPvcDiscardedRcvOamCells
catsPvcDiscardedRcvOamCells.description: The number of OAM cells that had CRC errors and are not counted in any other counters for received OAM cells.

catsPvcAisSuppressCnts.name: catsPvcAisSuppressCnts
catsPvcAisSuppressCnts.description: The number of instances that an ATM AIS alarm was successfully suppressed which prevented the alarm from propagating to the TDM interfaces.

catsPvcXmtAisCnts.name: catsPvcXmtAisCnts
catsPvcXmtAisCnts.description: The number of instances that an ATM AIS alarm was transmitted.

catsPvcRcvAisCnts.name: catsPvcRcvAisCnts
catsPvcRcvAisCnts.description: The number of instances that an ATM AIS alarm was received.

catsPvcXmtFerfCnts.name: catsPvcXmtFerfCnts
catsPvcXmtFerfCnts.description: The number of instances that an ATM FERF alarm was transmitted.

catsPvcRcvFerfCnts.name: catsPvcRcvFerfCnts
catsPvcRcvFerfCnts.description: The number of instances that an ATM FERF alarm was received.

catsPvcXmtAisCells.name: catsPvcXmtAisCells
catsPvcXmtAisCells.description: The number of AIS cells that were transmitted on this connection during this 15 minute interval.

catsPvcRcvAisCells.name: catsPvcRcvAisCells
catsPvcRcvAisCells.description: The number of AIS cells that were received on this connection during this 15 minute interval.

catsPvcXmtFerfCells.name: catsPvcXmtFerfCells
catsPvcXmtFerfCells.description: The number of FERF cells that were transmitted on this connection during this 15 minute interval.

catsPvcRcvFerfCells.name: catsPvcRcvFerfCells
catsPvcRcvFerfCells.description: The number of FERF cells that were received on this connection during this 15 minute interval.

catsPvcOamLpbkTimeoutCnts.name: catsPvcOamLpbkTimeoutCnts
catsPvcOamLpbkTimeoutCnts.description: The number of instances that OAM Loopback Timeout alarm had occurred within this 15 minute interval.

catsPvcNewOamLpbkTimeoutDur.name: catsPvcNewOamLpbkTimeoutDur
catsPvcNewOamLpbkTimeoutDur.description: The duration of new OAM Loopback Timeout alarms for this 15 minute interval expressed in seconds.

catsPvcActiveOamLpbkTimeoutDur.name: catsPvcActiveOamLpbkTimeoutDur
catsPvcActiveOamLpbkTimeoutDur.description: The total duration of new and past OAM loopback timeout alarms that were active during this 15 minute interval. For example, if the an alarm lasted for a total of 50 seconds and crossed interval boundaries. In the previous 15 minute interval it lasted for 30 seconds and 20 seconds in the current 15 minute interval. There is a new alarm that lasted for 15 seconds in the current 15 minute interval as well. Thus, this object will have a value of 20+15 = 35 seconds.

catsPvcOamLpbkTimeoutThreshold.name: catsPvcOamLpbkTimeoutThreshold
catsPvcOamLpbkTimeoutThreshold.description: This is the threshold for OAM Loopback Timeout alarm expressed in seconds. If the OAM cell is not received back within the threshold specified in this object, an OAM loopback timeout alarm is generated.

catsAal2PvcVpi.name: catsAal2PvcVpi

catsAal2PvcVci.name: catsAal2PvcVci

catsAal2PvcCpsSentPkts.name: catsAal2PvcCpsSentPkts
catsAal2PvcCpsSentPkts.description: The number of AAL2 CPS packets sent to the network during this 15 minute interval.

catsAal2PvcCpsRcvdPkts.name: catsAal2PvcCpsRcvdPkts
catsAal2PvcCpsRcvdPkts.description: The number of AAL2 CPS packets received from the network during this 15 minute interval. This does not include the packets which are counted as error packets.

catsAal2PvcHecErrors.name: catsAal2PvcHecErrors
catsAal2PvcHecErrors.description: The number of egress AAL2(ATM Adaptation layer 2) CPS PDU dropped due to HEC error.

catsAal2PvcCrcErrors.name: catsAal2PvcCrcErrors
catsAal2PvcCrcErrors.description: The number of egress AAL2 Type3 CPS PDUs dropped due to invalid CRC-10 error. CRC validation is for Type 3 packets only. Type 1 packets are not subjected to CRC-10 error validation. This does not count the Type 3 packets generated by the DSP.

catsAal2PvcInvOsfCells.name: catsAal2PvcInvOsfCells
catsAal2PvcInvOsfCells.description: The number of AAL2 cells dropped due to invalid OSF (OffSet Field) in the egress direction.

catsAal2PvcInvParCells.name: catsAal2PvcInvParCells
catsAal2PvcInvParCells.description: The number of AAL2 cells dropped due to invalid parity bit field in the egress direction.

catsAal2PvcCpsInvCidPkts.name: catsAal2PvcCpsInvCidPkts
catsAal2PvcCpsInvCidPkts.description: The number of AAL2 CPS packets dropped in the egress direction due to invalid CID(Channel Identifier). The CID may be considered as invalid if it is out of range or not configured.

catsAal2PvcCpsInvUuiPkts.name: catsAal2PvcCpsInvUuiPkts
catsAal2PvcCpsInvUuiPkts.description: The number of AAL2 CPS packets dropped in the egress direction due to invalid UUI field.

catsAal2PvcCpsInvLenPkts.name: catsAal2PvcCpsInvLenPkts
catsAal2PvcCpsInvLenPkts.description: The number of AAL2 CPS packets dropped in the egress direction due to invalid length field.

catsAal5PvcVpi.name: catsAal5PvcVpi
catsAal5PvcVpi.description: The VPI value for the AAL5 PVC for which the statistics are being collected.

catsAal5PvcVci.name: catsAal5PvcVci
catsAal5PvcVci.description: The VCI value for the AAL5 PVC for which the statistics are being collected.

catsAal5PvcIntervalIndex.name: catsAal5PvcIntervalIndex
catsAal5PvcIntervalIndex.description: This is the history interval number. The intervals are 15 minutes long and thus for a 24 hour period there will be 96 intervals. The 24 hour interval is aligned to wall clock. The index of 1 will represent the interval from 00:00 to 00:15. The index of 2 will represent the interval from 00:15 to 00:30 and so on.

catsAal5PvcValidFlag.name: catsAal5PvcValidFlag
catsAal5PvcValidFlag.description: This object is used to indicate if the entry has valid statistics data. It contains a value of true(1) if the data is valid and false(2) otherwise. A possible scenario when this flag will be set to false(2) is when there are time changes due to daylight savings time and/ or time zone changes. This flag can also be set to false(2) if statistics in this 15 minute interval have experienced discontinuity.

catsAal5PvcDiscontinuityTime.name: catsAal5PvcDiscontinuityTime

If this has the default value then it indicates that the statistics in this interval have not experienced any discontinuity.

catsAal5PvcPduSentPkts.name: catsAal5PvcPduSentPkts
catsAal5PvcPduSentPkts.description: The number of AAL5 PDUs transmitted to the network. This is applicable only to the PVCs configured as AAL5 PVCs (VoIP(Voice Over IP) PVCs or CCS PVCs in the case of VoAAL2 application).

catsAal5PvcPduRcvdPkts.name: catsAal5PvcPduRcvdPkts
catsAal5PvcPduRcvdPkts.description: The number of AAL5 PDUs received from the network. This is applicable only to the PVCs configured as AAL5 PVCs (VoIP(Voice Over IP) PVCs or CCS(Common Channel Signaling) PVCs in the case of VoAAL2 application).

catsAal5PvcInvCpiPdus.name: catsAal5PvcInvCpiPdus
catsAal5PvcInvCpiPdus.description: The number of AAL5 PDUs dropped in the egress direction due to invalid CPI(Common Part Indicator) field in the AAL5 PDU trailer. This is applicable only to the PVCs configured as AAL5 PVCs (VoIP(Voice Over IP) PVCs or CCS(Common Channel Signaling) PVCs in the case of VoAAL2 application).

catsAal5PvcOverSizedSDUs.name: catsAal5PvcOverSizedSDUs
catsAal5PvcOverSizedSDUs.description: The number AAL5 PDUs discarded on this AAL5 PVC at the interface associated with an AAL5 entity because the AAL5 SDUs were too large.

catsAal5PvcInvLenPdus.name: catsAal5PvcInvLenPdus
catsAal5PvcInvLenPdus.description: The number of AAL5 PDUs dropped due to length violations. This is applicable to CCS PVCs. The HDLC frames should have a minimum frame size in order for the proper interpretation by the upper layer protocol.

catsAal5PvcCrc32ErrorPdus.name: catsAal5PvcCrc32ErrorPdus
catsAal5PvcCrc32ErrorPdus.description: The number of AAL5 PDUs dropped in the egress direction due to CRC-32 errors detected by the SAR.

catsAal5PvcReassemTimerExpiryPdus.name: catsAal5PvcReassemTimerExpiryPdus
catsAal5PvcReassemTimerExpiryPdus.description: The number of AAL5 PDU reassembly timer expirations. The timers are maintained in the egress direction for building an AAL5 PDU from the cells.

catsCidHistoryTable.name: catsCidHistoryTable
catsCidHistoryTable.description: This table represents a 24 hour history of statistics per CID. The statistics are collected using 15 minute intervals. The Channel IDentification (CID) is the standard term to identify an ATM AAL2 connection (ITU-T I.366.2). CID is unique within a VC (SVC or PVC). Entries in this table are populated at the end of the interval.

catsCidHistoryEntry.name: catsCidHistoryEntry
catsCidHistoryEntry.description: An entry in the table. Each entry contains the statistics for a particular CID for the given 15 minute interval. The primary index, ifIndex, will be of ifType propAtm(197), atm(37) or aal2(37).

catsCidVpi.name: catsCidVpi
catsCidVpi.description: The VPI value of the ATM trunk connection with the CID for which the statistics are being collected.

catsCidVci.name: catsCidVci
catsCidVci.description: The VCI value of the ATM trunk connection with the CID for which the statistics are being collected.

catsCid.name: catsCid
catsCid.description: This object is the CID of an ATM AAL2 connection for which the statistics are being collected.

catsCidIntervalIndex.name: catsCidIntervalIndex
catsCidIntervalIndex.description: This is the history interval number. The intervals are 15 minutes long and thus for a 24 hour period there will be 96 intervals. The 24 hour interval is aligned to wall clock. The index of 1 will represent the interval from 00:00 to 00:15. The index of 2 will represent the interval from 00:15 to 00:30 and so on.

catsCidValidFlag.name: catsCidValidFlag
catsCidValidFlag.description: This object is used to indicate if the entry has valid statistics data. It will take a value of true(1) if the data is valid and false(2) otherwise. A possible scenario when this flag will be set to false(2) is when there are time changes due to daylight savings time and/ or time zone changes. This flag can also be set to false(2) if statistics in this 15 minute interval have experienced discontinuity.

catsCidDiscontinuityTime.name: catsCidDiscontinuityTime
catsCidDiscontinuityTime.description: This object will represent the timestamp when the statistics in this 15 minute interval were discontinued due to a forced clear on the module. If this has the default value then it indicates that the statistics in this interval have not experienced any discontinuity.

catsCidAvgSentPkts.name: catsCidAvgSentPkts
catsCidAvgSentPkts.description: This attribute defines the average packets per second sent towards the network in this 15 minute interval. The average is computed by dividing the total number of packets sent over this 15 minute interval by the interval time (15 minutes).

catsCidAvgRcvdPkts.name: catsCidAvgRcvdPkts
catsCidAvgRcvdPkts.description: This attribute defines the average packets per second received from the network in this 15 minute interval. The average is computed by dividing the total number of packets received over this 15 minute interval by the interval time (15 minutes).

catsCidSentPkts.name: catsCidSentPkts
catsCidSentPkts.description: This attribute defines the count of packets sent towards the network in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidRcvdPkts.name: catsCidRcvdPkts
catsCidRcvdPkts.description: This attribute defines the count of packets received from the network in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidSentOctets.name: catsCidSentOctets
catsCidSentOctets.description: This attribute defines the count of bytes sent towards the network in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidRcvdOctets.name: catsCidRcvdOctets
catsCidRcvdOctets.description: This attribute defines the count of bytes received from the network in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidSentPeakPkts.name: catsCidSentPeakPkts
catsCidSentPeakPkts.description: This attribute defines the peak packets per second sent towards the network in this 15 minute interval. The sent packets per second are monitored every second and the peak value over the 15 minute interval is returned in this object.

catsCidRcvdPeakPkts.name: catsCidRcvdPeakPkts
catsCidRcvdPeakPkts.description: This attribute defines the peak packets per second received from the network in this 15 minute interval. The received packets per second are monitored every second and the peak value over the 15 minute interval is returned in this object.

catsCidExtAISRcvdPkts.name: catsCidExtAISRcvdPkts
catsCidExtAISRcvdPkts.description: This object contains the number of external AIS AAL2 Type3 packets received in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidExtRAIRcvdPkts.name: catsCidExtRAIRcvdPkts
catsCidExtRAIRcvdPkts.description: This object contains the number of external RAI AAL2 Type3 packets received in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidExtConnAISRcvdPkts.name: catsCidExtConnAISRcvdPkts
catsCidExtConnAISRcvdPkts.description: This object contains the number of external connection AIS AAL2 Type2 packets received in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidExtConnRDIRcvdPkts.name: catsCidExtConnRDIRcvdPkts
catsCidExtConnRDIRcvdPkts.description: This object contains the number of External Connection RDI (Remote Defect Ind.) AAL2 Type2 packets received in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidExtAISRcvCnts.name: catsCidExtAISRcvCnts
catsCidExtAISRcvCnts.description: This object contains the count of external AIS AAL2 Type3 packets received in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidExtRAIRcvCnts.name: catsCidExtRAIRcvCnts
catsCidExtRAIRcvCnts.description: This object contains the number of external RAI AAL2 Type3 packets received in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidExtConnAISCnts.name: catsCidExtConnAISCnts
catsCidExtConnAISCnts.description: This object contains count of external connection AIS AAL2 Type2 packets received in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidExtConnRDICnts.name: catsCidExtConnRDICnts
catsCidExtConnRDICnts.description: This object contains the count of external connection RDI (Remote Defect Ind.) AAL2 Type2 packets received in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidExtAISXmtCnts.name: catsCidExtAISXmtCnts
catsCidExtAISXmtCnts.description: This object contains the count of external AIS AAL2 Type3 packets transmitted in this 15 minute interval.

catsCidExtRAIXmtCnts.name: catsCidExtRAIXmtCnts
catsCidExtRAIXmtCnts.description: This object contains the count of external RAI AAL2 Type3 packets transmitted in this 15 minute interval.
